A 28-year-old man has been arrested in connection with an alleged sexual offence on board a train.
British Transport Police said the incident took place on the 19:45 Glasgow Central to Largs service at about 20:15 on Tuesday 5 May.
The man is also alleged to have been involved in a trespassing incident on the service as it travelled between Johnstone and Glengarnock stations.
He is expected to appear at Paisley Sheriff Court on Friday.
